race.comment: MASSIRA (7) has been easily accounted for at his last two runs, both in Saturday company. Defeated 17 rivals three back in a Highway over 1000m on a wet track at Randwick. That provides a strong form reference - can win with a repeat of that effort. KIMBERLEY SECRETS (3) added to her run of minor placings when beaten under a length over this distance at Wyong (metro) last time out. Down in grade and looks nicely treated after Keatings' claim. Will look the winner at some stage. REMEMBER JACK (11) has been freshened up since a moderate effort over 1200m here five weeks ago. Enjoys getting his toe in the ground so this evening's conditions suit. ZARAGOZA (4) has been attacking the line well of late without threatening. Will be giving away a start again but is one to watch for in the closing stages. FINE VINTAGE (1) was brave in defeat over 1250m here last time. The winner of four from nine at this distance so third-up he comes right into calculations.
